ecv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_8jwx2IVseg1rEISXDJr7lm1p|fc_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0ab666f08197ad2d8ae28cbd88b0\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Compiled from \\\"Server.java\\\"\\npublic abstract class io.grpc.Server {\\n  public io.grpc.Server();\\n  public abstract io.grpc.Server start() throws java.io.IOException;\\n  public int getPort();\\n  public java.util.List<? extends java.net.SocketAddress> getListenSockets();\\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerServiceDefinition> getServices();\\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerServiceDefinition> getImmutableServices();\\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerServiceDefinition> getMutableServices();\\n  public abstract io.grpc.Server shutdown();\\n  public abstract io.grpc.Server shutdownNow();\\n  public abstract boolean isShutdown();\\n  public abstract boolean isTerminated();\\n  public abstract boolean awaitTermination(long, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit) throws java.lang.InterruptedException;\\n  public abstract void awaitTermination() throws java.lang.InterruptedException;\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778191031764}}\n6539:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating protobuf classes**\\n\\nI'm considering public protobuf generated classes under `io.grpc.alts.internal`. Even though \\\"internal\\\" is in the package name, they could be public. The user is seeking the library's public API, but the ALTS handshaker protocol is meant to be internal. While dynamic coverage might allow for use, existing tests don't import the internal classes. There are some limitations regarding reflection, so maybe I should stick to the documentation of grpc-java. There are also ambiguities about public vs. internal classes.\\n\\n**Considering test coverage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether to add a test for `InternalCheckGcpEnvironment.isOnGcp()`. It returns a boolean but it's tricky to assert the environment. I could check if it's stable between calls, as it reads a sys file under native conditions. Also, I might want to test `AltsChannelBuilder.forTarget` since existing tests only use `forAddress`. But does that make it too similar to what’s already covered? I need to be mindful not to duplicate tests, yet adding missing factory variants could be justified.\\n\\n**Evaluating service registration tests**\\n\\nI'm realizing that the existing tests for `AltsServerBuilder` cover forwarding options but not service registration or interceptors. Since the method is public, I could build and start a server to assert that `server.getServices()` includes the correct service after it starts. I don't need a client for this. However, I’m concerned about whether this test would duplicate the checks already in place, especially since it will inherently involve starting the server again. It might be a slight overlap.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0aa221c08197824a9e7a46001459\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_Qq2bQFn5lJ2hUr43Y4kyL_83TzRt5GqY0ku4jGgY3sTqyS_UomW3xDXJeWvx6WobqfHiFJH8SSWkSWxWv7pZErZKh0jis252VLUH6QiJaUdCwCY22ZTnkqIALsqRqYFgwljw3WOz0GolQR_zCPNTbhGiqtnAucW4tMeLFeaXfd5b9oOotpUposPwOxYkUHdqL1yk0XiJ5h9MiWsvPzljlcn9VQmX5x3jVN2qgBypz92aD4HvkdjNQp1_XN_g3nig4kuf3FMK992GOM3Fb2nYMoeAygX35iCfIIP0NkO1vOXdz5tVCznLEdLadndxWiIlKnl8mFKMlygBn5N4_GsHXVVRBM0g8f3s_vWvpDI6qF8VBzni33uLK-5W4al9q9_s034rELC3wu2sN6GvCaR9aHoNqXTWQRSs7XN9v09xaHN1rMZzyux6KblEup6PFL3tbjyEKq9w4pos6JBQHAt7JmzhGdMo5QeEmI9xYLd4yzFsGeJemXPt7tB6-5isWKLx7HiHMmPO7BVW38Mn5HezKQF_O2Vhp_8OWr-PU5fsTAHnDiVeWEPHcq5pF_fxX3wVxSP7oWh7BEh88usSAf6nWm5NeIXOPpA33JQ4mpAeotjD45DXdeKuY0HwGafWr4fUmPXK0v0U1wlOXPkaMCv5wekyzCjMyiCFXfJ2zF6U8EcRm9z3W7KjK_4y0Yat4f3DO63Fcpwk1Zxfim3itg08xfaK5jwwSpevMcNhqm_mbDiDufSt0_hCbMrm2L4yLpd6fD9R9CKsMpZwboNjxUl7VbZyBviLugelw1F-U69QGSOFJCft