d be justified.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating service registration tests**\\\\n\\\\nI'm realizing that the existing tests for `AltsServerBuilder` cover forwarding options but not service registration or interceptors. Since the method is public, I could build and start a server to assert that `server.getServices()` includes the correct service after it starts. I don't need a client for this. However, I’m concerned about whether this test would duplicate the checks already in place, especially since it will inherently involve starting the server again. It might be a slight overlap.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_8jwx2IVseg1rEISXDJr7lm1p|fc_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0ab666f08197ad2d8ae28cbd88b0\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/io.grpc/grpc-api/1.71.0/*/grpc-api-1.71.0.jar -public io.grpc.Server | sed -n '1,120p'\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 849, \"output\": 1207, \"cacheRead\": 29184, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 31240, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778191007887, \"responseId\": \"resp_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0aa142a08197b2d0fabe73d67271\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_8jwx2IVseg1rEISXDJr7lm1p|fc_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0ab666f08197ad2d8ae28cbd88b0\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Compiled from \\\"Server.java\\\"\\npublic abstract class io.grpc.Server {\\n  public io.grpc.Server();\\n  public abstract io.grpc.Server start() throws java.io.IOException;\\n  public int getPort();\\n  public java.util.List<? extends java.net.SocketAddress> getListenSockets();\\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerServiceDefinition> getServices();\\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerService